  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> </font><b>Datta,\n        dayadhvam, damyata</b> <b>...</b><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>'Datta, dayadhvam, damyata' (Give, sympathise,\n        control). The fable of the meaning of the Thunder is\n        found in the <i>Brihadaranyaka </i>- <i>Upanishad</i>, 5,\n        I. A translation is found in Deussen's S<i>echzig\n        Upanishads des Veda,</i> p. 489 [Eliot's note].</p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td> </td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Datta, dayadhvam, damyata ... 'Datta, dayadhvam, damyata' (Give, sympathise, control). The fable of the meaning of the Thunder is found in the Brihadaranyaka - Upanishad , 5, I. A translation is found in Deussen's S echzig Upanishads des Veda, p. 489 [Eliot's note]. back to \"The Waste Land\"",
